        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/microsoft-white-house-offer-cybersecurity-biden-nadella">
                                    Biden Asked Microsoft to “Raise the Bar on Cybersecurity.” He May Have Helped Create an Illegal Monopoly.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            When the White House welcomed Microsoft’s offer of $150 million in tech services, it helped the world’s largest software provider tighten its grip on federal business and freeze out competitors.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/renee-dudley">Renee Dudley</a>, with research by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/doris-burke">Doris Burke</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-11-15EST06:00">Nov. 15, 6 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

