        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/tennessee-school-threats-arresting-kids-with-disabilities">
                                    A 13-Year-Old With Autism Got Arrested After His Backpack Sparked Fear. Only His Stuffed Bunny Was Inside.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Disability rights advocates said kids like Ty should not be getting arrested under Tennessee’s school threats law. And they tried to push for a broader exception for kids with other kinds of disabilities. It didn’t work.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/aliyya-swaby">Aliyya Swaby</a>, ProPublica, and <span class="name">Paige Pfleger</span>, WPLN/Nashville Public Radio,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-11-13EST05:00">Nov. 13, 5 a.m. EST</time>
